#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10003
#: 54184626209047c19b66dd55f4cb39cb
msgid "Introduction to the Bass Diffusion Model"
msgstr "Introducción al Modelo de Difusión de Bass"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10005
#: f724f8780d294649bfeec906c4049188
msgid "What is the Bass Model?"
msgstr "¿Qué es el Modelo de Bass?"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10007
#: f169af7f099743d7bc37756da7253275
msgid ""
"The Bass diffusion model, developed by Frank Bass in 1969, is a mathematical"
" model that describes how new products get adopted in a population over "
"time. It's widely used in marketing to forecast sales of new products, "
"especially when historical data is limited or non-existent."
msgstr ""
"El modelo de difusión de Bass, desarrollado por Frank Bass en 1969, es un "
"modelo matemático que describe cómo los nuevos productos son adoptados en "
"una población a lo largo del tiempo. Se utiliza ampliamente en marketing "
"para prever las ventas de nuevos productos, especialmente cuando los datos "
"históricos son limitados o inexistentes."

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10009
#: 8af59fde7e1449cf9c52dfc18b129879
msgid ""
"The model captures the entire lifecycle of product adoption, from "
"introduction to saturation, making it a powerful tool for product planning "
"and marketing strategy development."
msgstr ""
"El modelo captura todo el ciclo de vida de la adopción del producto, desde "
"la introducción hasta la saturación, convirtiéndolo en una herramienta "
"poderosa para la planificación de productos y el desarrollo de estrategias "
"de marketing."

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10011
#: d7b8b0d74d85411bb99af447e2bd11e5
msgid "The Motivation Behind the Bass Model"
msgstr "La motivación detrás del modelo Bass"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10013
#: 3cddbe46ba3c481da7160eee66fa4934
msgid ""
"Before the Bass model, companies struggled to predict the adoption patterns "
"of new products. Traditional forecasting methods often failed because they "
"couldn't account for the social dynamics that drive product adoption. Frank "
"Bass recognized that product adoption follows a distinct pattern:"
msgstr ""
"Antes del modelo de Bass, las empresas luchaban por predecir los patrones de"
" adopción de nuevos productos. Los métodos de pronóstico tradicionales a "
"menudo fallaban porque no podían tener en cuenta las dinámicas sociales que "
"impulsan la adopción de productos. Frank Bass reconoció que la adopción de "
"productos sigue un patrón distinto:"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10015
#: 6ce075bfede541b9a7c5332f2d94b4e8
msgid ""
"**Initial slow growth**: When a product first launches, adoption starts "
"slowly"
msgstr ""
"**Crecimiento inicial lento**: Cuando un producto se lanza por primera vez, "
"la adopción comienza lentamente."

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10016
#: 07f1565bebc744fca6231acdc4633d4d
msgid ""
"**Rapid acceleration**: As more people adopt, word-of-mouth spreads and "
"adoption accelerates"
msgstr ""
"**Aceleración rápida**: A medida que más personas adoptan, el boca a boca se"
" difunde y la adopción se acelera."

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10017
#: 6511d28e907c47c0890e63acbd837ba9
msgid ""
"**Eventual saturation**: Eventually, the market becomes saturated and "
"adoption slows down"
msgstr ""
"**Saturación eventual**: Eventualmente, el mercado se satura y la adopción "
"se ralentiza."

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10019
#: c9ec301cbfd34e15ae749967a62bbcd1
msgid ""
"The Bass model provides a mathematical framework to capture these patterns, "
"enabling businesses to make more informed decisions about production "
"planning, inventory management, and marketing resource allocation."
msgstr ""
"El modelo de Bass proporciona un marco matemático para capturar estos "
"patrones, lo que permite a las empresas tomar decisiones más informadas "
"sobre la planificación de la producción, la gestión de inventarios y la "
"asignación de recursos de marketing."

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10021
#: 03e28917a49f4cd9ad456df623d7e30f
msgid "Mathematical Formulation"
msgstr "Formulación Matemática"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10023
#: da59db61d5724b149439186a1b9810e6
msgid ""
"The Bass model is based on a differential equation that describes the rate "
"of adoption:"
msgstr ""
"El modelo de Bass se basa en una ecuación diferencial que describe la tasa "
"de adopción:"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10025
#: 72f8d008efa74bbf8f306dadafa36366
#, python-brace-format
msgid "\\frac{f(t)}{1-F(t)} = p + q F(t)"
msgstr "\\frac{f(t)}{1-F(t)} = p + q F(t)"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10027
#: 02aa39f1e4284aebb6eb85aed9eb4359
msgid "Where:"
msgstr "Dónde:"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10029
#: 124797dbc7284bb1b492d3001978d990
msgid ""
"$F(t)$ is the installed base fraction (cumulative proportion of adopters)"
msgstr ""
"$F(t)$ es la fracción de base instalada (proporción acumulativa de "
"adoptantes)"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10030
#: 4809938b3fa3452a81f3728307c8b655
msgid ""
"$f(t)$ is the rate of change of the installed base fraction ($f(t) = F'(t)$)"
msgstr ""
"$f(t)$ es la tasa de cambio de la fracción de la base instalada ($f(t) = "
"F'(t)$)"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10031
#: 1aaf6c2059a14f42a4c83f06b1676097
msgid "$p$ is the coefficient of innovation or external influence"
msgstr "$p$ es el coeficiente de innovación o influencia externa"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10032
#: 7d8a792738954d72873231b7f4db6fc6
msgid "$q$ is the coefficient of imitation or internal influence"
msgstr "$q$ es el coeficiente de imitación o influencia interna"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10034
#: 8cdfb19a56734a6d8bcfa89b9ab8d503
msgid "The solution to this equation gives the adoption curve:"
msgstr "La solución a esta ecuación proporciona la curva de adopción:"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10036
#: 9ae7b294088145d88a589b34ff9835c7
msgid "F(t) = \\frac{1 - e^{-(p+q)t}}{1 + (\\frac{q}{p})e^{-(p+q)t}}"
msgstr "F(t) = \\frac{1 - e^{-(p+q)t}}{1 + (\\frac{q}{p})e^{-(p+q)t}}"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10038
#: 207609fff92848d7bb4de372b8835c09
msgid "The adoption rate at time $t$ is given by:"
msgstr "La tasa de adopción en el tiempo $t$ se da por:"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10040
#: b12054652b16478bbadae539384b9fbd
msgid "f(t) = (p + q F(t))(1 - F(t))"
msgstr "f(t) = (p + q F(t))(1 - F(t))"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10042
#: 3dcc7c47a9ce454aa67ac80bd105da44
msgid "Alternatively, this can be written as:"
msgstr "Alternativamente, esto se puede escribir como:"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10044
#: 925e9a14ab6342f4be953039493b208c
msgid ""
"f(t) = \\frac{(p+q)^2 \\cdot e^{-(p+q)t}}{p \\cdot "
"(1+\\frac{q}{p}e^{-(p+q)t})^2}"
msgstr ""
"f(t) = \\frac{(p+q)^2 \\cdot e^{-(p+q)t}}{p \\cdot "
"(1+\\frac{q}{p}e^{-(p+q)t})^2}"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10046
#: 9a3ed7a293c34c6d8a34557ae7895aa4
msgid "Key Components of the Bass Model Implementation"
msgstr "Componentes Clave de la Implementación del Modelo Bass"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10048
#: a9664c47a7fd4f3a97e535e22d093869
msgid ""
"The Bass model implementation in PyMC-Marketing consists of several key "
"components:"
msgstr ""
"La implementación del modelo Bass en PyMC-Marketing consiste en varios "
"componentes clave:"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10050
#: d32e280a59a64166846ff219650017b8
msgid "**Adopters** - The number of new adoptions at time $t$:"
msgstr "**Adoptantes** - El número de nuevas adopciones en el momento $t$:"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10052
#: cd06494cf1c14b03af2240bab338d47a
#, python-brace-format
msgid "\\text{adopters}(t) = m \\cdot f(p, q, t)"
msgstr "\\text{adopters}(t) = m \\cdot f(p, q, t)"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10054
#: eb0d8988039f43579c3fdf1d85937d45
msgid ""
"**Innovators** - Adoptions driven by external influence (advertising, etc.):"
msgstr ""
"**Innovadores** - Adopciones impulsadas por influencia externa (publicidad, "
"etc.):"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10056
#: aa65ee78fffb4f319b912ff0fd27277c
#, python-brace-format
msgid "\\text{innovators}(t) = m \\cdot p \\cdot (1 - F(p, q, t))"
msgstr "\\text{innovators}(t) = m \\cdot p \\cdot (1 - F(p, q, t))"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10058
#: 5eb251f6325b4703a530ad457c0aee0b
msgid ""
"**Imitators** - Adoptions driven by internal influence (word-of-mouth):"
msgstr ""
"**Imitadores** - Adopciones impulsadas por influencia interna (boca a boca):"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10060
#: 5bfb0fb3e67a4379b7e47900646083bd
#, python-brace-format
msgid "\\text{imitators}(t) = m \\cdot q \\cdot F(p, q, t) \\cdot (1 - F(p, q, t))"
msgstr "\\text{imitators}(t) = m \\cdot q \\cdot F(p, q, t) \\cdot (1 - F(p, q, t))"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10062
#: 1035e4ed65d04588a107619c720e6c9e
msgid "**Peak Adoption Time** - When the adoption rate reaches its maximum:"
msgstr ""
"**Hora de Adopción Máxima** - Cuando la tasa de adopción alcanza su máximo:"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10064
#: 3ecd48655f134ec9962acfe73f278e56
#, python-brace-format
msgid "\\text{peak} = \\frac{\\ln(q) - \\ln(p)}{p + q}"
msgstr "\\text{peak} = \\frac{\\ln(q) - \\ln(p)}{p + q}"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10066
#: cd84eeeb1a5e4f4b86d9f0792a092f42
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The total number of adopters over time is the sum of innovators and "
"imitators, which equals $\\text{adopters}(t)$. All of these components are "
"directly implemented in the PyMC model, allowing us to analyze each aspect "
"of the diffusion process separately."
msgstr ""
"El número total de adoptantes a lo largo del tiempo es la suma de "
"innovadores e imitadores, lo que equivale a $\\text{adopters}(t)$. Todos "
"estos componentes están implementados directamente en el modelo de PyMC, lo "
"que nos permite analizar cada aspecto del proceso de difusión por separado."

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10068
#: 65f671bcd433499a809bb3f3792b5b3b
msgid "Understanding the Relationship Between Components"
msgstr "Comprendiendo la Relación Entre los Componentes"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10070
#: 5dd7195b86ae459ebee9f74ef0150f42
msgid ""
"A key insight of the Bass model is how it decomposes adoption into two "
"sources:"
msgstr ""
"Una idea clave del modelo de Bass es cómo descompone la adopción en dos "
"fuentes:"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10072
#: 1601068fbeaa4fe4a28da20ce674dddd
#, python-brace-format
msgid "\\text{adopters}(t) = \\text{innovators}(t) + \\text{imitators}(t)"
msgstr "\\text{adopters}(t) = \\text{innovators}(t) + \\text{imitators}(t)"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10074
#: 6ab50b735cdc491587527ab6e308dc24
msgid "At each time point:"
msgstr "En cada punto temporal:"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10076
#: 699312fd6e594092ad5f8e4de99e7b9b
msgid ""
"**Innovators** ($m \\cdot p \\cdot (1 - F(t))$) represents new adoptions "
"coming from people who are influenced by external factors like advertising"
msgstr ""
"**Innovadores** ($m \\cdot p \\cdot (1 - F(t))$) representa nuevas "
"adopciones provenientes de personas que están influenciadas por factores "
"externos como la publicidad."

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10077
#: 5fbf4101f3c244ad9f8e4c96e89478f3
msgid ""
"**Imitators** ($m \\cdot q \\cdot F(t) \\cdot (1 - F(t))$) represents new "
"adoptions coming from people who are influenced by previous adopters"
msgstr ""
"**Imitadores** ($m \\cdot q \\cdot F(t) \\cdot (1 - F(t))$) representa las "
"nuevas adopciones que provienen de personas que están influenciadas por los "
"adoptantes anteriores."

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10079
#: 1584b7ed16da4e93907033ba78d817ee
msgid "As time progresses:"
msgstr "A medida que avanza el tiempo:"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10081
#: 5850ed8535894d88b35ea12d1a80e850
msgid ""
"Initially, **innovators** dominate the adoption process when few people have"
" adopted ($F(t)$ is small)"
msgstr ""
"Inicialmente, **los innovadores** dominan el proceso de adopción cuando "
"pocas personas han adoptado ($F(t)$ es pequeño)"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10082
#: b79f86c79f6347fcb9e836487783b594
msgid ""
"Later, **imitators** become the primary source of new adoptions as the word-"
"of-mouth effect grows"
msgstr ""
"Más tarde, los **imitadores** se convierten en la fuente principal de nuevas"
" adopciones a medida que crece el efecto de boca a boca."

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10083
#: cca8dd6c931e487f825f8d6a378cffdc
msgid ""
"Eventually, both decrease as the market approaches saturation ($F(t)$ "
"approaches 1)"
msgstr ""
"Eventualmente, ambos disminuyen a medida que el mercado se acerca a la "
"saturación ($F(t)$ se aproxima a 1)"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10085
#: 87e3c3e371bf43b8875f79ecc32fa6a4
msgid "The **cumulative adoption** at any time point is:"
msgstr "La **adopción acumulativa** en cualquier momento es:"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10087
#: 311c4411f52c416d8588df9565b4e5a1
#, python-brace-format
msgid "\\text{Cumulative Adoption}(t) = m \\cdot F(t)"
msgstr "\\text{Cumulative Adoption}(t) = m \\cdot F(t)"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10089
#: 407d33aa8e3c4d2488f32c18ee83d2f9
msgid ""
"This means that as $t \\to \\infty$, the cumulative adoption approaches the "
"total market potential $m$:"
msgstr ""
"Esto significa que a medida que $t \\to \\infty$, la adopción acumulativa se"
" aproxima al potencial total del mercado $m$:"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10091
#: ab33e841a26c4344bebe4e791d1a3f0f
#, python-brace-format
msgid "\\lim_{t \\to \\infty} \\text{Cumulative Adoption}(t) = m"
msgstr "\\lim_{t \\to \\infty} \\text{Cumulative Adoption}(t) = m"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10093
#: 70bea935695644ada317c52b812563fa
msgid ""
"Therefore, the Bass model provides a complete accounting of the market:"
msgstr ""
"Por lo tanto, el modelo de Bass proporciona un análisis completo del "
"mercado:"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10095
#: 421bcf0459ab44c4acf768a4c68810ad
msgid "At each time point, new adopters are either innovators or imitators"
msgstr "En cada momento, los nuevos adoptantes son innovadores o imitadores."

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10096
#: f4ca0fb099a040f5b7b76321c0666152
msgid ""
"Over the entire product lifecycle, all potential adopters (m) eventually "
"adopt the product"
msgstr ""
"A lo largo de todo el ciclo de vida del producto, todos los posibles "
"adoptantes (m) eventualmente adoptan el producto."

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10097
#: 4df074c340464d65b1182d290c604ebb
msgid ""
"The model tracks both the adoption rate (new adopters per time period) and "
"the cumulative adoption (total adopters to date)"
msgstr ""
"El modelo rastrea tanto la tasa de adopción (nuevos adoptantes por período "
"de tiempo) como la adopción acumulativa (total de adoptantes hasta la "
"fecha)."

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10099
#: e84b190f7c7f48dea9dce3c0dc43bc82
msgid ""
"This structure enables marketers to understand not just how many people will"
" adopt over time, but also the driving forces behind adoption at different "
"stages of the product lifecycle."
msgstr ""
"Esta estructura permite a los comercializadores comprender no solo cuántas "
"personas adoptarán a lo largo del tiempo, sino también las fuerzas "
"impulsoras detrás de la adopción en diferentes etapas del ciclo de vida del "
"producto."

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10101
#: 0e58d11f08484ad087f9d4c2a1789136
msgid "Understanding the Key Parameters"
msgstr "Comprendiendo los Parámetros Clave"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10103
#: d35769520a544d27abd232b44787b687
msgid "The model has three main parameters:"
msgstr "El modelo tiene tres parámetros principales:"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10105
#: 1a559b25075e4e56823f57672fedce1d
msgid ""
"**Market potential (m)**: Total number of eventual adopters (the ultimate "
"market size)"
msgstr ""
"**Potencial de mercado (m)**: Número total de adoptantes eventuales (el "
"tamaño final del mercado)"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10106
#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:130004
#: 9fb4c2736f4d4082861a0a8b835bbf03 ae8d9e6d33f8403280b336c6e4dd2b4c
msgid ""
"**Innovation coefficient (p)**: Measures external influence like advertising"
" and media - typically $0.01-0.03$"
msgstr ""
"**Coeficiente de innovación (p)**: Mide la influencia externa como la "
"publicidad y los medios - típicamente $0.01-0.03$"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10107
#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:130005
#: d5f78aa59b654c43b9dc1292c46071fc e4af6ccd2e484433892d5bb091b16791
msgid ""
"**Imitation coefficient (q)**: Measures internal influence like word-of-"
"mouth - typically $0.3-0.5$"
msgstr ""
"**Coeficiente de imitación (q)**: Mide la influencia interna como el boca a "
"boca - típicamente $0.3-0.5$"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10109
#: 8480c525fd16472ab95a16cd712249d2
msgid "Parameter Interpretation"
msgstr "Interpretación de Parámetros"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10111
#: 50db0e7e54714cd398834e3d80e13278
msgid ""
"A higher **p** value indicates stronger external influence (advertising, "
"marketing)"
msgstr ""
"Un valor **p** más alto indica una influencia externa más fuerte "
"(publicidad, marketing)"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10112
#: af62729e962f48ee835531050380d0c5
msgid ""
"A higher **q** value indicates stronger internal influence (word-of-mouth, "
"social interactions)"
msgstr ""
"Un valor **q** más alto indica una influencia interna más fuerte (boca a "
"boca, interacciones sociales)"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10113
#: 7fe2143a97a44ae89edcf68d0e0cdeca
msgid ""
"The ratio **q/p** indicates the relative strength of internal vs. external "
"influences"
msgstr ""
"La relación **q/p** indica la fuerza relativa de las influencias internas "
"frente a las externas."

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10114
#: a2fdc8fd5e8349e6bf0eee61d7c325ec
msgid "The peak of adoption occurs at time"
msgstr "El pico de adopción ocurre en el momento {like_this}."

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10116
#: f72f7910a6cd46b3911a9d76f906f6e0
#, python-brace-format
msgid "t^* = \\frac{\\ln(q / p)}{p + q}"
msgstr "t^* = \\frac{\\ln(q / p)}{p + q}"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10118
#: abeb8bedd1ec4579852f3e58c589fcb8
msgid "Innovators vs. Imitators"
msgstr "Innovadores vs. Imitadores"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10120
#: 00a0cf76a4ff474ab5e4d89613e12722
msgid "The Bass model distinguishes between two types of adopters:"
msgstr "El modelo de Bass distingue entre dos tipos de adoptantes:"

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10122
#: aa27f428b34c4267b2ba644f47935b7b
msgid ""
"**Innovators**: People who adopt independently of others' decisions, "
"influenced mainly by mass media and external communications"
msgstr ""
"**Innovadores**: Personas que adoptan independientemente de las decisiones "
"de otros, influenciadas principalmente por los medios de comunicación "
"masivos y las comunicaciones externas."

#: ../source/notebooks/bass/bass_example.ipynb:10123
#: 8375810e8ab3420ebea4474cb715aee7
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Mathematically represented as: $\\text{innovators}(t) = m \\cdot p \\cdot (1"
" - F(p, q, t))$"
msgstr ""
